"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-nepathya-to-perform-at-the-seoul-olympic-park\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Sept 19: Nepal's premier folk rock band is set to travel to South Korea to perform at the Olympic Hall of Seoul Olympic Park.  Nepathya will perform at the renowned Seoul Olympic Park\\u00a0also known as\\u00a0Olpark is an Olympic Park built to host the 1988 Summer Olympics. In 2011, the Olympic hall was renovated by the Korean Government converting it into a concert hall. Musicians of international acclaim like Deep Purple, Judas Priest, Mariah Carey, Air Supply have performed there since.  This is to be Nepathya's 5th\\u00a0appearance in the South Korean capital Seoul. \\\"We came here for the first time in 2005 and since then Seoul has played regular host to us. Our last show was at the prestigious KBS Arena, and now we are performing at the Olympic Hall. We are glad to be raising the bar of Nepali shows there.\\\" Said Kiran Krishna Shrestha of nepa~laya, the promoters of Nepathya.  \\\"I am thankful to all our listeners living in Nepal and beyond for accepting our music with such affection'', said Nepathya front man Amrit Gurung. \\\"We are glad to be performing in Seoul for the fifth time during Nepathya's 25 years of Music.\\\" He added.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availabil